<h3>Delete Functions</h3>
	<p>Similarly to the groups of output and input functions, there are three families of functions 
	that are used to delete characters from the screen.  One family is used to delete a single 
	character, one for deleting a line, and a group of functions for clearig entire screen.  The 
	delete functios do not have as many variants as the output and input functions.</p>
	
	<h4>Delete a Character</h4>
	<p>The functions <code>delch()</code> and <code>wdelch()</code> are used to delete a character at the 
	current position of the cursor.  When the character is deleted the characters to the right of the 
	one deleted are shifted to the left.  <code>mvdelch()</code> and <code>mvwdelch</code> move the 
	cursor before deleting the character.</p>
	<pre>
	int main(){
	   initscr();
	   
	   mvprintw(5, 0, "Curses");
	   getch();  //used to pause screen
	   move(5, 1);
	   delch();
	   
	   refresh();
	   return 0;
	}
	</pre>
