	<h4>Delete a Line</h4>
	<p> The functions <code>deleteln()</code> and <code>wdeleteln()</code> are used to delete the line where 
	the cursor currently is.  The lines after the one deleted are moved to fill where the removed line 
	was.  The delete line functions do not have a variant for performing a move and delete in one function 
	call.</p>
	<pre>
	int main(){
	   initscr();
	   
	   mvprintw(5, 0, "Line1");
	   mvprintw(6, 0, "Line2");
	   mvprintw(7, 0, "Line3");
	   getch();  //used to pause screen
	   move(6, 0);
	   deleteln();
	   
	   refresh();
	   return 0;
	}
	</pre>
