	<h4>Clearing the Window</h4>
	<p>The functions <code>clear()</code> and <code>wclear()</code> are used to clear every position 
	in the window.  There is an other set of  functions for clearing the screen.  <code>erase()</code> 
	and <code>werase()</code> clear the window and redraw it when <code>refesh()</code> is called next.  
	I have not noticed a difference between <code>clear()</code> and <code>erase()</code>.  The difference 
	will probably be noticable in large applications that putting large amounts of information in the 
	window.</p>
	<pre>
	int main(){
	   initscr();
	   
	   printw("Curses");
	   getch();  //used to pause screen
	   clear();
	   
	   refresh();
	   return 0;
	}
	</pre>
